Gauteng Premier David Makhura visited malls in Johannesburg to monitor compliance with updated lockdown regulations. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura on Wednesday visited two shopping centres to make sure shop owners and shoppers are complying with the rules and regulations of the lockdown under Alert Level Four. Eight other MECs will be visiting a number of other malls across Gauteng. COVID-19: Makhura says job losses inevitable Makhura made his way through a number of shops at Shoshanguve shopping centre, making sure all shop owners adhere to the rules. Malls seem to also be busier, but the premier said he is happy overall with the compliance of most shops. Makhura was also checking to make sure all goods sold are fresh and not expired after a number of shops were found to be selling rotten food. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.